Whitespace preservation covers the entire <pre> subtree, not just direct
children: a nested element's children glue verbatim, and the printer never
injects line breaks (significant whitespace) anywhere under the preserve root.
The whole file is already canonical — fmt must be a byte-for-byte no-op.
-- input.gsx --
package p

const snippet = `go install example.com/tool@latest
tool init`

component C() {
	<pre class="snippet"><code>{ snippet }</code></pre>
	<pre><code>
  <span>one</span> two
</code></pre>
}
-- fmt.golden --
package p

const snippet = `go install example.com/tool@latest
tool init`

component C() {
	<pre class="snippet"><code>{ snippet }</code></pre>
	<pre><code>
  <span>one</span> two
</code></pre>
}
